# Intro

Data from data.world [makeover monday](https://data.world/makeovermonday/2018-w-4-turkey-vulture-migration-in-north-and-south-america)

Data originally from [movebank](https://www.movebank.org/)

And published here: http://rstb.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/369/1643/20130195

# Set Up


```r
library(tidyverse)
library(parsedate)
library(lubridate)
```


# Data


```r
turkeys <- read.delim("../sketch4/data/Turkey vultures in North and South America - migration.csv", sep = ",", header=T)
```

## Break apart and make date data useful


```r
fulldate <- parse_iso_8601(turkeys$timestamp)
datesplit <-  t(as.data.frame(strsplit(as.character(fulldate), split = " ")))
rownames(datesplit) <- NULL
colnames(datesplit) <- c("date", "hour")
turkeys <- cbind(datesplit, turkeys)
turkeys <- turkeys %>% mutate(month = month(date, label=TRUE), year = year(date))
```


# Analysis

I ended the previous sketch by looking at the turkey migration over time by using facet wrap. 
That's a reasonable, and perhaps more clear way than what I am about to do.

But in order to make it the most clear...



```r
turkeys %>% filter(animal.id == "Morongo") %>% group_by(month, year) %>%
  summarise(n_dates = n_distinct(date))
```

```
## # A tibble: 37 x 3
## # Groups:   month [?]
##    month  year n_dates
##    <ord> <dbl>   <int>
##  1   Jan  2007      30
##  2   Jan  2008      31
##  3   Jan  2009      31
##  4   Feb  2007      25
##  5   Feb  2008      29
##  6   Feb  2009      28
##  7   Mar  2007      30
##  8   Mar  2008      31
##  9   Mar  2009      31
## 10   Apr  2006      21
## # ... with 27 more rows
```



```r
library(plot3D)
```


```r
morongo <- turkeys %>% filter(animal.id == "Morongo")
points3D(x = morongo$location.long, y = morongo$location.lat, z = morongo$event.id, phi = 10, theta = 90)
```

![](sketch5-turkeys2_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png)<!-- -->

Here, because I cannot get this graph to use month as a color variable, red is the most resent time, and blue is the older time.

Just a reminder:


```r
turkeys %>% filter(animal.id == "Morongo") %>% ggplot(aes(x=location.long, y=location.lat, color=month)) + geom_point()
```

![](sketch5-turkeys2_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png)<!-- -->

Ok, I don't like plot3D that much. So far, it's been fairly unimpressive to me.

So, let's try plotly!


```r
library(plotly)
```

plotting offline for now


```r
p <- plot_ly(morongo,x = ~location.long, y = ~location.lat, z = ~event.id, color = ~month) %>%
  add_markers() %>%
  layout(scene = list(xaxis = list(title = 'Longitude'),
                     yaxis = list(title = 'Latitude'),
                     zaxis = list(title = 'Time')))
p
```
